iances they have formed (such as OPEC and CIPEC). Finally he offers suggestions for cooperative action that could both serve the needs of the less developed areas and promote international harmony.Practical in approach and original in concept, the book clarifies complex contemporary problems and points the way toward solving them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aInternational economic relations. 0aNatural resources. 0aWorld politicsy1965-1975. 4aEnvironmental History. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aNATURE / Natural Resources.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150174268240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501742682423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501742682.jpg  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK